rComments: Although she is passionate at what she does, she was not effective at communicating it. The timetable says that you do not need any musical understanding for this class. Well someone should have told her that. She focused heavily on the music and didn't give definitions of the terms she was using for those people who are not musically inclined.
teacherRatingTags: ['Beware of pop quizzes', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: If you are interested in Music History, then you will love her classes. The lectures are very interesting, and instead of writing a final paper, she wanted to switch things up and allowed the students to choose their own creative project. She is really a professional in her field.

Clark was an adequate professor and seemed very interested in the topic (opera) but exams were very difficult for the uninitiated and turned out to not only have a lot of trivia but require (without being told about this ahead of time) a lot of memorization of weird Italian names/terms.

Not a fan. She breezes past interesting subject matter and spends half the course talking about historical roles of women in society. After being told to memorize half the text for the midterm, nearly none of that information proved relevant. Though she's obviously a very smart prof, I think she belongs in a research library, not a lecture hall.
